   <p class="p1">Anyone who has ever needed to alter a node form knows how difficult it can be to get it to cooperate. However, paired with Display Suite and Field Group, Renderable Entities gives users the ability to format the display of just about <em style="font-size: 1.6rem; line-height: 2.4rem;">any</em> form built using the Form API, including node forms. This is nice because it adds all of the standard Drupal fields and module fields like the published checkbox, URL alias settings and allows you to rearrange them just as you would on the "manage display" screen of a node.... <a href="/blog/ian-whitcomb/drupal-form-layouts-renderable-entities" class="more-link">Read more</a></p>
